## Phase 2: Leads Database Setup 📊

### Headers

- [ ] **Step 2.1** — go to "Leads Database" sheet
- [ ] **Step 2.2** — enter column headers in row 1
  - A1: Lead ID
  - B1: Date Received
  - C1: Date Entered
  - D1: Property Name
  - E1: Address
  - F1: City
  - G1: State
  - H1: Asset Type
  - I1: Asking Price
  - J1: Number of Units/Pads/Sites
  - K1: Acreage
  - L1: NOI
  - M1: Occupancy / Vacancy
  - N1: Broker Name
  - O1: Broker Phone
  - P1: Sender Name
  - Q1: Sender Email
  - R1: Attachments Received
  - S1: Missing Docs Flag
  - T1: Missing Docs List
  - U1: Seller Financing Mention
  - V1: Summary of Opportunity
  - W1: Intake Status
  - X1: Follow-Up Status
  - Y1: Human Review Flag
  - Z1: Last Follow-Up Date
  - AA1: Assigned To
  - AB1: Notes

### Data Validation (Dropdowns)

- [ ] **Step 2.3** — Set up dropdown for Column H (Asset Type)
  - Select H2:H1000
  - Data → Validation
  - Choose: List of items
  - Enter: RV Park, Campground, Resort
  - Save

- [ ] **Step 2.4** — Set up dropdown for Column W (Intake Status)
  - Select W2:W1000
  - Data → Validation
  - Choose: List of items
  - Enter: New, In Progress, Waiting on Docs, Ready for Review, Human Review Needed, Completed
  - Save

- [ ] **Step 2.5** — Set up dropdown for Column X (Follow-Up Status)
  - Select X2:X1000
  - Data → Validation
  - Choose: List of items
  - Enter: No Follow-up Sent, Follow-up Sent, Follow-up in Progress, Completed
  - Save

### Test Data (Optional but recommended)

- [ ] **Step 2.6** — Add at least 5-10 test leads
  - Use realistic sample data
  - Mix of asset types (RV Parks, Campgrounds, Resorts)
  - Vary dates, statuses, flags
  - Include some with missing docs, human review flags, etc.

