## Phase 3: Dashboard Sheet - Header & KPIs 🎨

### Switch to "New Leads Dashboard" sheet

- [ ] **Step 3.1** — Click the "New Leads Dashboard" tab at bottom

### SECTION A — Header (Rows 1-3)

- [ ] **Step 3.2** — Row 1: Main Title
  - Merge cells A1:G1
  - Content: "New Leads Dashboard"
  - Format: Bold, 18pt, white text, navy blue background (#1a3a5f)
  - Row height: 36pt

- [ ] **Step 3.3** — Row 2: Subtitle
  - Merge cells A2:G2
  - Content: "Keystone Acquisitions Intake Monitoring"
  - Format: 11pt, gray text (#555555), italic, navy blue background
  - Row height: 24pt

- [ ] **Step 3.4** — Row 3: Last Updated
  - Cell A3: "Last Updated:"
  - Cell B3: =TEXT(NOW(),"MMM DD, YYYY at h:mm AM/PM")
  - Format: 9pt
  - Background: Light gray (#f9f9f9)
  - Add bottom border (light gray)

### SECTION B — KPI Cards (Rows 5-9)

- [ ] **Step 3.5** — Row 5: KPI Labels
  - A5: Total New Leads
  - B5: Leads Today
  - C5: Leads This Week
  - D5: Leads This Month
  - E5: Missing Docs
  - F5: Awaiting Follow-Up
  - G5: Human Review
  - Format: Bold, 10pt, centered, light gray background (#d3d3d3)
  - Row height: 20pt

- [ ] **Step 3.6** — Row 6: KPI Formulas (First Row)
  - A6: =COUNTA('Leads Database'!A2:A)
  - B6: =COUNTIFS('Leads Database'!B:B,TODAY())
  - C6: =COUNTIFS('Leads Database'!B:B,">="&TODAY()-6,'Leads Database'!B:B,"<="&TODAY())
  - D6: =COUNTIFS('Leads Database'!B:B,">="&DATE(YEAR(TODAY()),MONTH(TODAY()),1),'Leads Database'!B:B,"<="&TODAY())
  - E6: =COUNTIF('Leads Database'!S:S,TRUE)
  - F6: =COUNTIFS('Leads Database'!S:S,TRUE,'Leads Database'!X:X,"<>Completed")
  - G6: =COUNTIF('Leads Database'!Y:Y,TRUE)
  - Format: Bold, 16pt, centered, light blue background (#e8f1f8), 2pt navy border
  - Row height: 40pt
  - Number format: 0 (integers)

- [ ] **Step 3.7** — Row 7: Secondary KPIs
  - A7: =COUNTIF('Leads Database'!H:H,"RV Park")
  - B7: =COUNTIF('Leads Database'!H:H,"Campground")
  - C7: =COUNTIF('Leads Database'!H:H,"Resort")
  - D7: =COUNTIF('Leads Database'!U:U,TRUE)
  - E7: =IF(A6=0,0,ROUND(E6/A6*100,1))&"%"
  - F7: =IF(A6=0,0,ROUND(G6/A6*100,1))&"%"
  - G7: =C6
  - Format: Bold, 11pt, centered, light gray background (#f0f0f0), 1pt gray border
  - Row height: 28pt

